In one early work of Rene Guenon, untranslated, he shares his plans to "infiltrate the theosophical society with the purpose of destroying it". He was good friends with an anti-masonic activist by the name of Olivier de Fremond, who introduced him to Catholic initiatory circles.

Fremond, together with a few others, attempted to dissuade Guenon from entering deeper into Sufism, but he did regardless, as he needed to be initiated into the chain. Guenon supposedly did pass the initiation to Evola, even though the two have never officially met in person.
If you want to look for legitimate initiation today, just go to the hesychasts of Mount Athos, any organization that claims or offers it otherwise will deceive you. But it's not for us anyways.

In the 80s, there was a big publicity campaign warning parents that giving aspirin to a child with the flu could cause the potentially deadly Reye syndrome. Aspirin sales declined sharply, as sales of acetaminophen (Tylenol, Paracetamol, etc.) increased tremendously.
But in Australia, a study of Reye syndrome cases found that SIX TIMES as many of them had been using acetaminophen as had used aspirin.
